{{Politics of the Central African Republic}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in the [[Central African Republic]] on 28 December 1994. The new constitution would make the country a [[presidential system|presidential]] republic with a [[unicameralism|unicameral]] National Assembly and a [[List of heads of government of the Central African Republic and Central African Empire|Prime Minister]] accountable to both the President and the National Assembly.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/cf.html Elections in the Central African Republic] African Elections Database</ref> It was approved by 82.7% of voters with a 45% turnout.
