{{Politics of Rwanda}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Rwanda]] on 17 December 1978. It followed a coup by [[Juvénal Habyarimana]] in 1973 and the dissolution of the former sole legal party, [[Parmehutu|MDR-Parmehutu]]. The new constitution created a presidential republic with no term limits for the [[List of Presidents of Rwanda|President]], and made the [[National Republican Movement for Democracy and Development|National Revolutionary Movement for Development]] the sole legal party. It was approved by 89.1% of voters.<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/rw.html Elections in Rwanda] African Elections Database</ref>
